cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

The paper deals with algorithms for computing simulation and bisimulation metrics for stochastic systems, which are relevant to various areas of computer science such as game theory, artificial intelligence, and logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves linear programming and computational geometry, which suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) as possible sub-categories.
